CSS TO LOOK AT

1. Perspective
2. Filters : filter: blur(5px), opp: filter: none
3. Blur
4. Aspect ratio: i.e aspect-ratio: 16/9: no need for height, this makes the image very responsive
5. Input: input:focus{outline: none}, ::placeholder, prop: caret-color: red
6. not, is, where i.e .item :is(h1){color: red}, .class :not(elem, elem2){}
7. .review:has(elem) .content{ filter: blur(20px)}

Aspect ration 16/9 means 16(w) and 9(h) or 16by9

<video controls src="./"> 
<track kind="captions"/>
</video>
video {
aspect-ratio: 16/9
}

